  "prompt": "How do I send gif in whatsapp?",
  "response": "Sending a GIF on WhatsApp is quite simple! Here's how you can do it on both mobile (Android/iOS) and desktop:\n\n### **On Mobile (Android/iOS):**\n1. **Open WhatsApp** and go to the chat where you want to send the GIF.\n2. **Tap the text input field** at the bottom of the chat.\n3. **Tap the Emoji/GIF button** (usually a smiling face or a GIF icon next to the text box).\n4. **Select the GIF tab** (it may appear as \"GIF\" or a magnifying glass icon).\n5. **Search for a GIF** using keywords or browse through the suggestions.\n6. **Tap the GIF** you want to send, and it will automatically be sent in the chat.\n\n### **On WhatsApp Desktop:**\n1. **Open WhatsApp** on your computer.\n2. **Go to the chat** where you want to send the GIF.\n3. **Click the Emoji/GIF button** (usually a smiling face or a GIF icon next to the text box).\n4. **Select the GIF tab** or search for a GIF using the search bar.\n5. **Click the GIF** you want to send, and it will be sent in the chat.\n\n### **Alternative Method (Using Gallery):**\nIf you have a GIF saved on your phone or computer:\n1. Open WhatsApp and go to the chat.\n2. Tap the **Attachment icon** (paperclip or \"+\" icon) in the chat window.\n3. Select **Gallery** or **Photos**.\n4. Choose the GIF file from your gallery and send it.\n\nThat's it! Your GIF will now be shared in the chat. \ud83c\udf89",
